04/02/2007
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Republika Srpska police smashed a drug smuggling ring, police chief Uros Pena announced on Saturday (February 3rd). 
He said the police detained nine persons in Eastern Sarajevo, Banja Luka, Brcko, Ugljevik and Derventa and seized over 3kg heroin, with a market value of some 150,000 euros. 
(Nezavisne novine - 04/02/07; RTRS, PBS BiH, NTV Hayat - 03/02/07)
